<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-18197] Builds being often aborted because of python3 ./scripts/gen-nodetool-docs.py being slow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18197</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18181&quot; title=&quot;Fix tests post JDK-8210522 (rewrite reflection of &amp;quot;modifiers&amp;quot; field)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18181&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18181&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, recently we see builds aborted as python3 ./scripts/gen-nodetool-docs.py is too slow. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; most of the time in the script is spent in create_adoc, which is serially forking nodetool help for every command to gather it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Anthony+Grasso&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Anthony Grasso&quot;&gt;Anthony Grasso&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
